#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:56
msgid ""
"If the file does not exist, VI opens a blank file and an empty page is "
"displayed on the screen. When the file is saved, it will take the name "
"specified with the command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:58
msgid ""
"If the command `vi` is executed without specifying a file name, VI opens a "
"blank file and an empty page is displayed on the screen. When the file is "
"saved, VI will ask for a file name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/05-vi.md:60
msgid ""
"The `vim` editor takes the interface and functions of VI with many "
"improvements."
msgstr ""

